[SN]TITLE[SN]
Watch Scottish Premiership matches on Sportscene at 18:00 on Sunday

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Sportscene features all of the weekend Scottish Premiership action in its new regular Sunday timeslot of 18:00 BST on BBC Two Scotland.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The programme is repeated on BBC One Scotland at 23:25 BST and available on demand from BBC iPlayer.
Sunday's programme features Aberdeen's trip to Celtic Park and Rangers' visit to Kilmarnock.
Hamilton hosted Ross County, Inverness took on St Johnstone, Motherwell met Dundee and Hearts met Partick Thistle.
